HEADWORD: Birlaw
<hw>Bir"law</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>By</er><er>-law</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A law made by
husbandmen respecting rural affairs; a rustic or local law or
by-law.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>byrlaw</asp>, <asp>birlie</asp>,
<asp>birley</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

